THE HIGHLANDS ENERGY GROUP LLC
Availability
The Highlands Energy Group LLC ("The Highlands Energy Group LLC") makes electric energy and capacity available under this Rate Schedule to any purchaser for resale.
Applicability
This Rate Schedule is applicable to all sales of energy or capacity by The Highlands Energy Group LLC not otherwise subject to a particular Rate Schedule of The Highlands Energy Group LLC.
Rates
All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and The Highlands Energy Group LLC.
Other Terms and conditions
All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and The Highlands Energy Group LLC.
Affiliate Sales Prohibited
No sale shall be made pursuant to this Rate Schedule to any public utility with a franchised electric service territory that is controlled by, or under common control with, or controlling The Highlands Energy Group LLC.
Effective Date
This Rate Schedule is effective on September 30, 2011 (the date set by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission).
Issued By: Kevin D. Gorman Effective: 9/30/2011 Managing Member Issued On: January 9, 2006 Revised on March 9, 2006
THE HIGHLANDS ENERGY GROUP LLC
1. Reporting to Commission of Certain Status Changes: Seller must timely report to the Commission any change in status that would reflect a departure from the characteristics the Commission relied upon in granting market-base rate authority. A change in status includes, but is not limited to, each of the following. (i) ownership or control of generation or transmission facilities or inputs to electric power production other than fuel supplies, or (ii) affiliation with any entity not disclosed in the application for market based rate authority that owns or controls generation or transmission facilities or inputs to electric power production, or affiliation with any entity that has a franchised service area. Any change in status must be filed no later than 30 days after the change in status occurs.
Issued By: Kevin D. Gorman Effective: 9/30/2011 Managing Member Issued On: January 9, 2006 Revised on March 9, 2006
